p","attrib":{},"text":"1989—Subsecs. (b)(3), (5), (c)(2)(A)(ii), (C). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/239/s7891/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–239, § 7891(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Internal Revenue Code of 1986” for “Internal Revenue Code of 1954”, which for purposes of codification was translated as “title 26” thus requiring no change in text."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/239/s7894/e/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–239, § 7894(e)(3)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated cls. (i) and (ii) as subpars. (A) and (B), respectively, struck out “, to the extent that such plan’s assets are held in one or more custodial accounts which qualify under section 401(f) or 408(h) of title 26, whichever is applicable” before the semicolon in subpar. (B), and inserted concluding provision “to the extent that such plan’s assets are held in one or more custodial accounts which qualify under section 401(f) or 408(h) of title 26, whichever is applicable.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(2)(A). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/239/s7894/e/1/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–239, § 7894(e)(1)(A)","children":[],"tail":", in introductory provisions, made technical amendment to reference to part 1 of subtitle E of subchapter III of this chapter to correct reference to corresponding part of original Act, requiring no change in text, and in cls. (i) and (ii), inserted “if such contribution or payment is” before “made by an employer”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(3), (4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/239/s7881/k"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–239, § 7881(k)","children":[],"tail":", redesignated par. (4) as (3) and struck out former par. (3) which read as follows: “In the case of a contribution which would otherwise be an excess contribution (as defined in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s4979/c"},"text":"section 4979(c) of title 26","children":[],"tail":") paragraph (1) shall not prohibit a correcting distribution with respect to such contribution from the plan to the employer to the extent permitted in such section to avoid payment of an excise tax on excess contributions under such section.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1987—Subsec. (c)(2)(B). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/203/s9343/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–203, § 9343(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", amended subpar. (B) generally. Prior to amendment, subpar. (B) read as follows: “If a contribution is conditioned on qualification of the plan under section 401, 403(a), or 405(a) of title 26, and if the plan does not qualify, then paragraph (1) shall not prohibit the return of such contributions to the employer within one year after the date of denial of qualification of the plan.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/203/s9343/c/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–203, § 9343(c)(2)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s4979/c"},"text":"section 4979(c) of title 26","children":[],"tail":"” for “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t26/s4972/b"},"text":"section 4972(b) of title 26","children":[],"tail":"”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1980—Subsec. (a)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/364/s402/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–364, § 402(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “chapter” for “subchapter”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(6). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/364/s411/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–364, § 411(c)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (6)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/364/s310/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–364, § 310(1)","children":[],"tail":", in